This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with face-related applications and synthesizing facial variations. It also involves the use of discriminators and generators, which are commonly used in GANs, making it likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper involves image processing and manipulation, which falls under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of generative models to address the lack of training data suggests that it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
